core_transport.documentation: Core plasma transport. Energy terms correspond to the full kinetic energy equation (i.e. the energy flux takes into account the energy transported by the particle flux)

core_transport.code.documentation: Generic decription of the code-specific parameters for the code that has produced this IDS

core_transport.code.output_flag.documentation: Output flag : 0 means the run is successful, other values mean some difficulty has been encountered, the exact meaning is then code specific. Negative values mean the result shall not be used.

core_transport.code.parameters.documentation: List of the code specific parameters in XML format

core_transport.ids_properties.documentation: Interface Data Structure properties. This element identifies the node above as an IDS

core_transport.ids_properties.comment.documentation: Any comment describing the content of this IDS

core_transport.ids_properties.creation_d.documentation: Date at which this data has been produced

core_transport.ids_properties.homogeneou.documentation: This node must be filled (with 0 or 1) for the IDS to be valid. If 1, the time of this IDS is homogeneous, i.e. the time values for this IDS are stored in the time node just below the root of this IDS. If 0, the time values are stored in the various time fields at lower levels in the tree. In the case only constant or static nodes are filled within the IDS, this node must still be filled, and set to 1 (by convention).

core_transport.ids_properties.provider.documentation: Name of the person in charge of producing this data

core_transport.ids_properties.source.documentation: Source of the data (any comment describing the origin of the data : code, path to diagnostic signals, processing method, ...)

core_transport.model.documentation: Transport is described by a combination of various transport models

core_transport.model[:].flux_multiplier.documentation: Multiplier applied to the particule flux when adding its contribution in the expression of the heat flux : can be 0, 3/2 or 5/2

core_transport.model[:].flux_multiplier_.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "flux_multiplier"

core_transport.model[:].identifier.index.documentation: Integer identifier (enumeration index within a list)

core_transport.model[:].profiles_1d.documentation: Transport coefficient profiles for various time slices. Fluxes and convection are positive (resp. negative) when outwards i.e. towards the LCFS (resp. inwards i.e.  towards the magnetic axes).

core_transport.model[:].profiles_1d[:].c.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "conductivity_parallel"
